column1: Class   Age       Squat   Bench   Dead    Total
*This meet was dedicated to the memory of our dear friend KAREN HIRASA who passed away earlier this year*

This year we finished a little later than last year's contest. We had a total of 44 lifters this year. We started lifting around 9:45 AM and were finished about 7:15 PM. Preparation and clean-ups were a lot smoother. Things will get better as we run more meets. A lot of good lifting as the USAPL dominates the Hawaii scene. Once again I'd like to thank some people who helped this event become a success. P.J. Couvillion, Nalei Harris, (Tony we missed ya this year) Candy Ford, Champ, Quincy Guzman, Glenn Toma, Gary Ferstler, Ed Morishima, Tommy Heffernan, Mike Saito, Nolan Crabbe, Rick Hayes, Da boys - Faima, Mesa, Bull, Darren, John, Brett, Habu, Koligi and her gang. Thanks to Anuhea and Gaylynn. My children Micah, Thea and Jonas for accepting their roles and a very special thanks to my right hand woman, my wife Leah (Hoochie Mama)
PS. Even though he wasn't feeling well at all, P.J. flew over from the big island to help me run this meet. I don't know what we'd do without him. It's nice to have someone memorize the kilo chart.
